The paper discusses the evaluation of generative models, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on evaluating image synthesis models, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also introduces a general evaluation framework that can be applied to continuous distributions, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), and statistics (cs.ST).
